name: DELTA Physical CD
description:
Delta is Shapeshifter's 5th studio album, released on 31st May, 2013.

Tracklisting
1:   Monarch
2:   Gravity
3:   Taste Of Memory
4:   Giving Up The Ghost
5:   In Colour
6:   Diamond Trade
7:   Arcadia
8:   Stadia
9:   Shadow Boxer
10: Little Flame
11: Endless
12: 141

Delta was recorded in Berlin, Woodhill and Wellington and features 'Monarch', ‘Diamond Trade’ plus the new single ‘Gravity’. 

The towering success of Christchurch-formed Shapeshifter can’t be denied. Across their career they have made genre-defining appearances at Glastonbury, The Big Chill, Big Day Out, Parklife plus sold-out performances across Europe. This is the fifth studio album from Shapeshifter, following the previous albums that have all achieved platinum status within New Zealand.

name: Shapeshifter - System Remix CD
description:
Back in December, Shapeshifter announced plans to free the stems of The System Is A Vampire's killer cut Longest Day for remixers and versionists worldwide, levelling the playing field so that any producer – irrespective of recognition or reputation – had the chance to sit alongside heavyweight production talent like Netsky, B-Complex, State Of Mind, and Camo & Crooked on Shapeshifter's boxfresh long player, System Remix.

The result? A stack of top shelf rerubs of Longest Day for the band to work their way through – and one reworking that stood head and shoulders above the rest

name: System is a Vampire CD
description:
System is a Vampire  
2009  
Truetone Recordings  

Opening album track ‘Dutchies’, PDigsss implores listeners to “Hold onto the vibe” – The System is a Vampire allows Shapeshifter’s legion of fans to do just that, translating their elemental powers onto record, a take-out version of the band’s live alchemy – never before has Shapeshifter bottled lightning quite like they have on this album. Like their live shows that consistently sell out across New Zealand and Australia, The System is a Vampire’s 11 tracks are calls-to-arms, instructions aimed at motivating bodies and minds.  

While Shapeshifter continue to set their own terms for their music and how it’s presented, this didn't stop The System is a Vampire debuting at number one on the New Zealand album charts. Its success has been as unstoppable as the rolling drum breaks that fuel Shapeshifter – the album was released on a Friday and by lunchtime had sold more albums than any other that week, going on to become their third LP to clock platinum sales.

name: Soulstice CD
description:
Soulstice  
2006  
Truetone Recordings  

Soulstice takes in influences from the world’s of soul, reggae, funk, rock and of course drum and bass, all rounded off with a superb sonic quality, unique to this band. Soulstice obtained Gold sales status in New Zealand in three weeks and has since achieved Platinum sales. Shapeshifter were awarded a phenomenal 3 awards at the New Zealand bnet (independent) music awards for Best Live Act, Song of the Year for “Bring Change” and Album of the Year for Soulstice and the New Zealand Music Award for Best Electronic Album.

name: Shapeshifter Live
description:
Shapeshifter Live  
2007  
Truetone Recordings  

Shapeshifter Live was recorded at the Christchurch Town Hall on the final show of their legendary sold out orchestra tour and in the band's hometown. This 6-track album contained a previously unreleased song called "Good Looking" and appeared along-side other popular Shapeshifter tracks such as "Tapestry", "Bring Change" and "One".

name: Riddimwise
description:
Riddim Wise  
2004  
Truetone Recordings  

Riddim Wise exhibits a definite step towards a more liquid funk style of drum'n'bass. Recorded at Shapeshifter’s own home studio in Melbourne, the album features collaborations with Aotearoa's most prodigious and exciting vocalists; Dallas Tamaira aka Joe Dukie (Fat Freddy's Drop), Ladi6 (Verse 2/Sheelahroc) and Paora Apera aka P Digsss. The album was praised as a steady progression from 'Realtime', with an emphasis on funky dancefloor grooves, whilst maintaining strong musical elements. The album became the #1 Independent NZ album release and also the #1 NZ National Dance Album in New Zealand history.

name: Shapeshifter - Realtime
description:
Realtime  
2001  
Truetone Recordings  

Realtime includes a collaboration with sublime vocalist Ladi6 on the track "Move With Me" as well as Kaps (Fabel) and Tiki (Salmonella Dub) on production. Realtime was awarded the 'Best Electronic Release' title at the 2002 BNet NZ Music Awards, and was also nominated at the RIANZ NZ Music Awards for 'Best Electronic Album’. The album is noted for its heavier sound compared with the band's more recent material.

name: Pacific Heights: In a Quiet Storm
description:
Pacific Heights is the solo project of Devin Abrams, a founding member of NZ's #1 live act and arguably most popular drum and bass outfit, Shapeshifter. Abrams released the Pacific Heights EP way back in the early noughties, following it with his debut album Frozen Fears – both releases sold in their thousands but are no longer available. While his earlier releases referenced D&B, this album shows another side of the multi-talented multi-instrumentalist.
In A Quiet Storm is an exquisite album which fuses nu soul and hip hop in a way no-one else in NZ has. With echoes of genre-defining artists such as Platinum Pied Pipers, Sa-Ra, Steve Spacek and Pete Rock, In A Quiet Storm blends this forward-thinking approach to sound with his distinctly Pacific flavoured beats and vibes.
The album features guest appearances from some of NZ's favourite vocalists, such as Joe Dukie (Fat Freddy’s Drop), PDigsss (Shapeshifter), Ladi 6 and Lisa Tomlins (Rhombus), alongside Mara TK (Electric Wire Hustle), Jetlag Johnson (Fat Freddy’s Drop), Mark Vanilau (Departure Lounge) and fresh new faces Sacha Vee, JDubs and Aeries.
Abrams is planning a nationwide tour during September – but this is no one man band business, no! Bringing In A Quiet Storm to the live stage is a superstar line up of NZ’s top soul artists, including Joe Dukie, PDigsss and Lisa Tomlins.
Pacific Heights is also joined at various venues around the country by the likes of Downtown Brown, Partido, Nick D, Isaac Aesili, Electric Wire Hustle and DJ Mu (Fat Freddys Drop).
